text: WATCH: A de-escalating strategy created by a community group in Chicago’s North Lawndale area introduces new cops to the neighborhood and the people who live in it through walking tours given by local teens. https://t.co/h5lTKYaWW0 - @NBCNightlyNews

name: NBCNews
text: Americans are used to knowing the results of a presidential election on Election Night. But a surge of mail-in votes amid the pandemic, and nuances to how they get counted per state, could delay the projection of results for days, if not longer. https://t.co/ln8R7LWIAX
